===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From Latinised Greek '''plectrum''', from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[πλήκτρον]]''' (''plektron'') "anything to strike with,  an instrument for striking the lyre, a spear point", from '''[[πλήσσω]]''' (''plesso'') "to strike, to smite, to sting".

===Noun===
'''plectrum''' or '''plectron''' (''Plural'' '''[[plectra]]''')
# a small piece of plastic, metal, ivory, etc for [[pluck]]ing the [[string]]s of a [[guitar]], [[lyre]], [[mandolin]], etc
# (''Anatomy'')(''Zoology'') an [[anatomical]] part resembling a [[plectrum]] in shape

